The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Fairlie Place peon held
                                                                                                               Fairlie Place peon held
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	A peon of the company that was robbed of Rs 30 lakh on Tuesday at its Fairlie Place office has been detained. Samir Manna, 21, kept changing his statements while describing the robbery, police said.         
	We suspect an insiders involvement and are verifying Mannas statement. We are also examining all 35 employees of the company, said city detective chief Jawed Shamim.        
	Three youths raided the office of Pangene Biotech Pvt Ltd at 10pm on Tuesday and held owner Shyam Sundar Lahoti and Manna at gunpoint while they were counting cash, and fled with the money.                                                                                                                                                                           
